        "username": "Howard_Cooper",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/howard_cooper/{size}/700_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-08-31T23:30:33.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This was my first wine ever from Domaine Guillemot-Michel.  It was very impressive for the price.  A very well balanced wine with beautiful rich flavors.  Did not have the complexity or the finish of a premier cru from the Cote du Beaune, but then again it is only three years old and I don\u2019t have any experience to know how long it will age and what it develops into with age.  It did pass the <span class=\"hashtag\">#1</span> and most difficult test - my wife liked it.   <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\"></p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T21:32:58.200Z",
        "reply_count": 1,
